OL,3,CLetby inquiry told steps should be
OL,4,Ctaken to root out 'bad apples' in the
OL,5,CNHS
OL,7,FAn expert witness told the Thirlwall
OL,8,FInquiry, the challenges of not
OL,9,Fidentifying them were illustrated by
OL,10,Fthe cases of Dr Harold Shipman and
OL,11,Fanother child killer nurse, Beverley
OL,12,FAllitt.
OL,14,FProfessor Mary Dixon-Woods, from the
OL,15,FUniversity of Cambridge, said a doctor
OL,16,Fwho began to suspect Allitt was
OL,17,Fharming infants in Grantham,
OL,18,FLincolnshire, in 1991 was "initially
OL,19,Ftreated as having fanciful ideas and
OL,20,Fwas not treated seriously".
OL,26,@zD@[OU|D@ZO]
