OL,3,CLetby inquiry told steps should be
OL,4,Ctaken to root out 'bad apples' in the
OL,5,CNHS
OL,7,FProf Dixon-Woods said: "Partly this
OL,8,Fwas because there wasn't a recognition
OL,9,Fthat bad apple behaviour can sometimes
OL,10,Fbe the source of problems because
OL,11,Fthere wasn't a very clear procedure
OL,12,Ffor dealing with it."
OL,14,FMeanwhile, Shipman was a "snake" who
OL,15,Fmanaged to wriggle through holes in
OL,16,Fpatient safety systems to commit his
OL,17,Fterrible actions before he was finally
OL,18,Fdetected, she said.
OL,26,@oD@XOUtD@UO]vD@ZOUvD@`O]
