OL,3,CLetby inquiry told steps should be
OL,4,Ctaken to root out 'bad apples' in the
OL,5,CNHS
OL,7,FExamples of bad apples were those who
OL,8,Fpersisted with grossly incompetent
OL,9,Fclinical practice or demonstrated
OL,10,Funacceptable behaviours such as
OL,11,Fbullying and racism, she said.
OL,13,FProf Dixon-Woods went on: "There are
OL,14,Falso those who demonstrate
OL,15,Ftransgressive behaviours which reach
OL,16,Fthe threshold for criminality and that
OL,17,Fmight include murder, assault, rape or
OL,18,Fother violations."
OL,26,@uD@[OUzD@RO]
