OL,3,CLetby inquiry told steps should be
OL,4,Ctaken to root out 'bad apples' in the
OL,5,CNHS
OL,7,FProf Dixon-Woods said: "I think the
OL,8,Fkey thing is that we recognise some of
OL,9,Fthe human behaviour that's involved in
OL,10,Fidentifying what may be a very unusual
OL,11,Fpattern of events.
OL,13,F"And the second thing is that there is
OL,14,Fa procedure for dealing with this. I
OL,15,Fthink our procedures for dealing with
OL,16,Fthese kind of very transgressive and
OL,17,Funusual incidents have remained
OL,18,Funderdeveloped in the NHS.
OL,26,@oD@XOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/10
