OL,3,CLetby inquiry told steps should be
OL,4,Ctaken to root out 'bad apples' in the
OL,5,CNHS
OL,7,F"The credibility gap typically appears
OL,8,Fwhen the issue at hand is so
OL,9,Fextraordinarily egregious that it is
OL,10,Fdifficult to believe that someone
OL,11,Fcould have committed it."
OL,13,FProf Dixon-Woods told inquiry chair
OL,14,FLady Justice Thirlwall that
OL,15,Ftransgressive behaviour was a "rare
OL,16,Fbut distinct class of patient safety
OL,17,Frisk that needs to be addressed with
OL,18,Fappropriate strategies, policies and
OL,19,Fprocesses that are standardised and
OL,20,Fproperly supported throughout the NHS."
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@YO]wD@_OU|D@gO]
